(47, 2, 14, 49, 5, 2, 2, 'savour of his knowledge', 'Triumph and Sweetsmelling Savour', 'This connection highlights the theme of a ''sweetsmelling savour'' in both passages, where 2 Corinthians speaks of the ''savour of his knowledge'' and Ephesians refers to Christ''s sacrifice as a ''sweetsmelling savour.'' Both emphasize the pleasing aroma associated with God''s work through Christ.', 'theme', 0.496, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 14, 45, 8, 37, 37, 'triumph in Christ', 'Triumph in Christ Connection', 'Both passages emphasize victory through Christ. 2 Corinthians highlights triumph in Christ, while Romans declares believers as more than conquerors through Him.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 14, 47, 2, 15, 16, 'savour of his knowledge', 'Triumph and Savor Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of triumph in Christ and the manifestation of His knowledge. Both passages emphasize being a ''savour'' of Christ, illustrating the dual response of those who encounter the message.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 14, 45, 6, 17, 17, 'thanks be unto God', 'Triumph and Obedience Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of gratitude towards God for transformation. Both passages express thanks for a change in status, from servitude to sin to triumph in Christ, emphasizing the importance of obedience to doctrine.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 14, 47, 9, 15, 15, 'thanks be unto God', 'Connection of Gratitude to God', 'Both passages emphasize giving thanks to God. The first passage expresses gratitude for triumph in Christ, while the second passage thanks God for his gift.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 14, 19, 106, 47, 47, 'triumph', 'Triumph and Praise Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of triumph in relation to God. 2 Corinthians speaks of triumph in Christ, while Psalms calls for triumph in praise. This connection highlights the continuity of celebrating God''s victory.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 14, 22, 1, 3, 3, 'savour of his knowledge', 'Connection of Savor and Triumph', 'This connection highlights the theme of ''savour'' in both passages, where the ''savour of his knowledge'' in 2 Corinthians parallels the ''savour of thy good ointments'' in Song of Solomon. Both emphasize the fragrant nature of divine presence and knowledge, evoking a response of love and admiration.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 15, 49, 5, 2, 2, 'sweet savour of Christ', 'Sweet Savour of Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a ''sweetsmelling savour'' to God, illustrating the pleasing nature of Christ''s sacrifice and the believers'' role in reflecting that aroma. This connection highlights the transformative impact of Christ''s love and sacrifice on both the saved and the perishing.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 15, 46, 1, 18, 18, 'in them that are saved', 'Connection of Salvation and Perishing', 'Both passages emphasize the contrasting responses to the message of Christ, highlighting that it is perceived as ''foolishness'' by those that perish, while being a ''sweet savour'' to those that are saved. This connection illustrates the duality of reception to the Gospel.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 15, 26, 20, 41, 41, 'sweet savour', 'Sweet Savour of God', 'This connection highlights the theme of being a ''sweet savour'' to God in both passages. In 2 Corinthians, believers are described as a sweet savour of Christ, while Ezekiel speaks of God accepting His people with their sweet savour. Both emphasize the pleasing nature of God''s relationship with His followers.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 15, 50, 4, 18, 18, 'sweet savour of Christ', 'Sweet Smell Sacrifice Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a ''sweet savour'' or ''odour of a sweet smell'' as pleasing to God. This connection highlights the idea of offerings and actions that are acceptable and well-pleasing to Him.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 15, 1, 8, 21, 21, 'sweet savour', 'Connection of Sweet Savour', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a ''sweet savour'' that is pleasing to God. In Genesis, it signifies God''s acceptance and mercy, while in 2 Corinthians, it represents the believers'' role in spreading the fragrance of Christ to others.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 15, 2, 29, 18, 18, 'sweet savour', 'Sweet Savour Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a ''sweet savour'' as an offering to God. In 2 Corinthians, believers are described as a sweet savour of Christ, paralleling the burnt offering in Exodus that is also termed a sweet savour.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 15, 53, 2, 10, 10, 'them that perish', 'Connection of Salvation and Perishing', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between those who are saved and those who perish. The phrase ''them that perish'' appears in both, linking the consequences of rejecting the truth and the nature of salvation.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 16, 47, 3, 5, 6, 'savour of life unto life', 'Sufficiency and Life Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between death and life, highlighting that our sufficiency comes from God, who gives life through the spirit. The ''savour of life'' in the first passage connects to the ''spirit'' that ''giveth life'' in the second.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 16, 43, 9, 39, 39, 'savour of death unto death', 'Judgment and Spiritual Perception', 'Both passages emphasize the contrasting outcomes of spiritual perception. In 2 Corinthians, the ''savour of death'' and ''savour of life'' reflect the judgment Jesus speaks of in John, where some gain sight while others are blinded.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 16, 60, 2, 7, 8, 'savour of death unto death', 'Savor of Life and Death', 'Both passages emphasize the contrasting responses to Christ. In 2 Corinthians, believers experience life, while disobedient individuals face death, paralleling the disallowed stone in 1 Peter that causes offense.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 16, 42, 2, 34, 34, 'savour of death unto death', 'Life and Death Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the duality of outcomes associated with Jesus. In 2 Corinthians, the ''savour of death unto death'' contrasts with the ''savour of life unto life,'' paralleling Simeon''s declaration of Jesus as ''set for the fall and rising again of many.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 16, 46, 15, 10, 10, NULL, 'Grace and Labor Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of grace in the believer''s life and ministry. In 2 Corinthians, the sufficiency for the task is questioned, while in 1 Corinthians, grace empowers labor. This connection highlights the transformative power of grace in contrasting outcomes.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 16, 44, 13, 45, 47, 'savour of life unto life', 'Savour of Life and Death', 'Both passages emphasize the contrasting responses to the message of salvation. In 2 Corinthians, the ''savour of life unto life'' reflects the positive reception of the Gospel, while ''savour of death unto death'' aligns with the Jews'' rejection in Acts, leading Paul to turn to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 16, 44, 20, 26, 27, 'savour of death unto death', 'Savor of Life and Death', 'This connection highlights the duality of responses to the message of God. In 2 Corinthians, the ''savour of death unto death'' and ''savour of life unto life'' reflects the urgency of declaring God''s counsel, as seen in Acts where Paul states he is ''pure from the blood of all men.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 17, 47, 4, 2, 2, NULL, 'Integrity in Handling Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize sincerity and truthfulness in communicating God''s word. They warn against deceitful practices and highlight the importance of integrity in ministry.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 17, 47, 1, 12, 12, NULL, 'Sincerity and Godly Conduct', 'Both passages emphasize sincerity and godly conduct in communication. They highlight the importance of speaking and living in a manner that reflects divine grace rather than human wisdom.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 17, 61, 2, 1, 3, 'corrupt the word of God', 'False Teachers and Sincerity', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of false teachers who corrupt the truth. 2 Corinthians warns against those who corrupt the word of God, while 2 Peter describes false prophets bringing in heresies, leading many astray.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 17, 55, 4, 3, 4, 'corrupt the word of God', 'Corruption of the Word', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of deviating from sound doctrine. 2 Corinthians warns against those who corrupt the word of God, while 2 Timothy describes a time when people will turn away from truth to fables.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 17, 54, 4, 1, 3, 'corrupt the word of God', 'Corruption of God''s Word', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of corrupting the truth of God. In 2 Corinthians, it warns against those who corrupt the word of God, while 1 Timothy describes those who depart from faith and follow misleading doctrines.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 17, 24, 5, 31, 31, 'corrupt the word of God', 'Corruption of God''s Word', 'This connection highlights the theme of corruption in the communication of God''s message. Both passages emphasize the presence of false prophets and the consequences of misleading teachings.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 2, 17, 24, 23, 27, 32, 'corrupt the word of God', 'Corruption of God''s Word', 'This connection highlights the theme of corrupting God''s word. Both passages address the issue of false prophets and the importance of speaking God''s word faithfully.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 1, 47, 12, 11, 11, 'commendation', 'Commendation and Apostolic Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the need for commendation. In 2 Corinthians 3:1, Paul questions the need for letters of commendation, while in 2 Corinthians 12:11, he expresses disappointment at not being commended by the Corinthians despite his apostolic credentials.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 1, 47, 10, 12, 12, 'commend ourselves', 'Self-Commendation and Comparison', 'Both passages emphasize the issue of self-commendation. In 2 Corinthians 3:1, Paul questions the need for letters of commendation, while in 2 Corinthians 10:12, he warns against those who commend themselves and compare themselves with others.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 1, 44, 18, 27, 27, 'letters of commendation', 'Letters of Commendation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of commendation through letters. In 2 Corinthians, Paul questions the need for letters of commendation, while in Acts, the brethren write to commend Apollos to the disciples in Achaia.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 1, 46, 16, 3, 3, 'letters of commendation', 'Letters of Commendation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of letters of commendation. Both passages discuss the approval and use of letters to validate authority and support.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 1, 46, 3, 10, 10, NULL, 'Commendation and Building Foundations', 'This connection highlights the theme of establishing credibility and authority in ministry. Both passages emphasize the importance of how one builds upon the foundation laid, suggesting a relationship between commendation and the integrity of one''s work.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 2, 46, 9, 1, 2, 'known and read of all men', 'Apostolic Validation Through Believers', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of believers as a testament to the apostolic ministry. In 2 Corinthians, Paul refers to believers as an ''epistle'' known by all, while in 1 Corinthians, he describes them as the ''seal'' of his apostleship, indicating their significance in validating his role.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 2, 45, 1, 8, 8, 'known and read of all men', 'Faith and Recognition', 'This connection highlights the idea of believers being recognized for their faith. Both passages emphasize how the actions and faith of individuals are known and acknowledged by others.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 2, 52, 1, 8, 8, 'known and read of all men', 'Faith and Witness in Community', 'This connection highlights the idea of believers being a testament to their faith. Both passages emphasize how the actions and faith of individuals are visible and impactful to others.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 2, 50, 1, 7, 7, 'in our hearts', 'Connection of Heartfelt Affection', 'Both passages emphasize the deep emotional bond between the writer and the recipients. The phrase ''in our hearts'' in 2 Corinthians 3:2 parallels ''have you in my heart'' in Philippians 1:7, highlighting the personal connection and mutual support in faith.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 2, 46, 3, 10, 10, 'known and read of all men', 'Building and Witnessing Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of building and being known. In 2 Corinthians, the believers are described as an epistle, suggesting they are a living testament, while in 1 Corinthians, the focus is on building a foundation, indicating the importance of how one constructs their faith.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 2, 47, 7, 3, 3, 'in our hearts', 'Connection of Heartfelt Affection', 'Both passages emphasize the deep emotional bond between Paul and the Corinthians. The phrase ''in our hearts'' in 2 Corinthians 7:3 connects to the idea of being ''written in our hearts'' in 2 Corinthians 3:2, highlighting their mutual relationship.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 2, 47, 11, 11, 11, NULL, 'Love and Recognition in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of recognition in relationships. Both passages emphasize the importance of being known and the expression of love within the community.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 3, 26, 11, 19, 19, NULL, 'Transformation of the Heart', 'This connection highlights the transformation from a ''stony heart'' to a ''heart of flesh'' as seen in both passages. Both emphasize the role of the Spirit in writing God''s message on the heart, indicating a shift from external to internal spiritual realities.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 3, 24, 31, 33, 33, NULL, 'Connection of Heart and Law', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s law being written in the hearts of His people. Both passages emphasize the transformation from external to internal, with the Spirit of God playing a crucial role in this process.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 3, 58, 8, 10, 10, 'fleshy tables of the heart', 'Connection of Heart and Law', 'Both passages emphasize the writing of God''s laws in the heart. 2 Corinthians speaks of ''fleshy tables of the heart,'' while Hebrews mentions writing laws ''in their hearts.'' This connection highlights the transformative nature of God''s covenant.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 3, 58, 10, 16, 16, 'in fleshy tables of the heart', 'Connection of Heart and Law', 'Both passages emphasize the writing of laws in the heart. 2 Corinthians speaks of the Spirit writing on ''fleshy tables of the heart,'' while Hebrews mentions putting laws ''into their hearts.''', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 3, 19, 40, 8, 8, 'fleshy tables of the heart', 'Law Written on Hearts', 'Both passages emphasize the internalization of God''s law, with 2 Corinthians highlighting the ''fleshy tables of the heart'' and Psalms expressing that ''thy law is within my heart.'' This connection highlights the transformative nature of divine guidance in believers.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 3, 2, 31, 18, 18, 'tables of stone', 'Connection of Written Testimony', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of written testimony, with Exodus referencing ''tables of stone'' and 2 Corinthians contrasting this with ''fleshy tables of the heart.'' This connection highlights the transition from the old covenant, symbolized by stone, to the new covenant, represented by the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 3, 2, 24, 12, 12, 'tables of stone', 'Connection of Written Law', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the law written on stone and the law written on hearts. Both passages emphasize the act of God writing His commandments, but 2 Corinthians focuses on a spiritual transformation rather than a physical inscription.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 4, 49, 3, 12, 12, 'trust have we through Christ', 'Access and Confidence in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of boldness and confidence in approaching God through faith in Christ. They highlight the believer''s trust and access to God, underscoring the relationship established through Christ.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 4, 50, 1, 6, 6, 'trust have we through Christ', 'Confidence in God''s Work', 'Both passages emphasize confidence in God''s faithfulness. 2 Corinthians 3:4 speaks of trust through Christ, while Philippians 1:6 expresses confidence that God will complete His work.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 4, 2, 18, 19, 19, 'to God-ward', 'Trust and Mediation to God', 'This connection highlights the theme of approaching God through mediation. Both passages emphasize the role of a mediator, with 2 Corinthians referencing trust through Christ and Exodus indicating a mediator for the people to God-ward.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 4, 47, 2, 14, 14, 'through Christ', 'Triumph Through Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Christ in enabling believers to have trust and experience triumph. The connection highlights how faith in Christ leads to a manifestation of God''s knowledge and victory in believers'' lives.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 4, 52, 1, 8, 8, 'to God-ward', 'Faith to God-ward Connection', 'Both passages emphasize faith directed towards God. In 2 Corinthians, trust is established through Christ to God-ward, while in 1 Thessalonians, the faith of the believers is also directed to God-ward, highlighting a shared theme of faithfulness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 3, 5, 47, 12, 9, 9, 'sufficiency is of God', 'Sufficiency in God''s Grace', 'Both passages emphasize that sufficiency comes from God. In 2 Corinthians 3:5, it states our sufficiency is of God, while 2 Corinthians 12:9 highlights that God''s grace is sufficient. This connection highlights the theme of divine strength in human weakness.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
