(47, 4, 2, 46, 4, 5, 5, 'hidden things of dishonesty', 'Hidden Things and Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the revelation of hidden truths. 2 Corinthians 4:2 speaks of renouncing dishonesty and manifesting truth, while 1 Corinthians 4:5 mentions bringing to light hidden things of darkness. This connection highlights the theme of transparency and divine judgment.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
