(47, 11, 4, 46, 12, 4, 11, 'another spirit, which ye have not received', 'Connection of Spirit and Gifts', 'This connection highlights the importance of the same Spirit in both passages. 2 Corinthians 11:4 warns against receiving another spirit, while 1 Corinthians 12:4-11 emphasizes the diverse gifts given by the same Spirit.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 4, 44, 4, 12, 12, 'another gospel, which ye have not accepted', 'Salvation and Another Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the exclusivity of salvation through Jesus. 2 Corinthians warns against accepting ''another Jesus'' or ''another gospel,'' while Acts asserts that salvation is found in no other name. This connection highlights the importance of adhering to the true message of Christ.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 4, 45, 8, 15, 15, 'another spirit, which ye have not received', 'Connection of Spirit and Adoption', 'This connection highlights the contrast between receiving a false spirit and the true Spirit of adoption. Both passages emphasize the importance of the spirit received by believers, with Romans affirming the positive aspect of receiving the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 5, 47, 12, 11, 12, NULL, 'Apostolic Authority and Signs', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s assertion of equality with the chief apostles. He claims he is not behind them, highlighting his credentials through signs and wonders.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 5, 46, 15, 10, 10, 'the very chiefest apostles', 'Apostolic Authority and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize the role of grace in establishing apostolic authority. Paul asserts he is not inferior to the chief apostles, attributing his labor to God''s grace.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 5, 48, 2, 6, 9, 'the very chiefest apostles', 'Apostolic Authority and Recognition', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of Paul among the apostles. In 2 Corinthians, Paul asserts he is not inferior to the chief apostles, while Galatians highlights the acknowledgment of his ministry by prominent figures like James and Peter.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 6, 46, 1, 17, 17, 'rude in speech', 'Connection of Speech and Knowledge', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of knowledge over eloquence. In 2 Corinthians, Paul acknowledges his ''rude in speech'' while asserting his knowledge, paralleling 1 Corinthians where he avoids ''wisdom of words'' to maintain the effectiveness of the gospel.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 6, 49, 3, 4, 4, 'not in knowledge', 'Knowledge of Christ''s Mystery', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of knowledge, with 2 Corinthians highlighting the speaker''s knowledge and Ephesians inviting readers to understand this knowledge in the mystery of Christ. This connection highlights the importance of understanding spiritual truths.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 6, 47, 4, 2, 2, 'made manifest', 'Manifestation of Truth', 'This connection highlights the theme of ''manifestation'' in both passages. In 2 Corinthians 11:6, Paul speaks of being made manifest in knowledge, while in 2 Corinthians 4:2, he emphasizes the manifestation of truth. Both verses underscore the importance of revealing truth and knowledge openly.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 6, 46, 2, 1, 3, 'rude in speech', 'Connection of Speech and Knowledge', 'Both passages emphasize the speaker''s lack of eloquence and reliance on divine knowledge. In 2 Corinthians, the speaker acknowledges being ''rude in speech,'' while in 1 Corinthians, he states he did not come with ''excellency of speech.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 6, 47, 5, 11, 11, 'made manifest', 'Manifestation of Knowledge', 'Both passages emphasize being made manifest, highlighting the revelation of knowledge and truth. The connection suggests a shared theme of transparency before God and others.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 6, 61, 3, 15, 16, 'not in knowledge', 'Connection of Knowledge and Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of knowledge and understanding in the context of teaching. Paul acknowledges his knowledge in 2 Corinthians, while Peter refers to Paul''s wisdom in 2 Peter, highlighting the challenge of understanding his writings.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 7, 47, 12, 13, 13, 'that ye might be exalted', 'Self-Exaltation and Burdens', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s refusal to be burdensome to the Corinthians while preaching the gospel. This connection highlights his humility and the contrast with other churches.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 7, 46, 4, 10, 12, 'abasing myself that ye might be exalted', 'Contrast of Strength and Weakness', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between the perceived strength of the Corinthians and the weakness of Paul and his companions. Paul highlights his own humility and suffering in service to the gospel, paralleling the depiction of the apostles as despised and weak yet faithful. This connection highlights the theme of self-abasement for the sake of others'' exaltation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 7, 46, 9, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Apostolic Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of apostles having the right to forbear working for their support. In 2 Corinthians, Paul questions if he has wronged them by not demanding compensation, while in 1 Corinthians, he asserts the authority he shares with Barnabas regarding their right to financial support.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 7, 47, 10, 1, 1, 'abasing myself', 'Meekness and Humility in Paul', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s humility and meekness. In 2 Corinthians 10:1, he describes himself as ''base among you,'' while in 11:7, he questions if he has offended by abasing himself for their benefit.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
