(47, 11, 7, 44, 18, 1, 3, 'preached to you the gospel of God freely', 'Paul''s Humility and Labor', 'This connection highlights Paul''s willingness to work for his sustenance while preaching the gospel freely. Both passages emphasize his commitment to serving others without financial gain, as seen in his relationship with Aquila and Priscilla.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 7, 44, 20, 34, 34, 'abasing myself that ye might be exalted', 'Self-Sacrifice in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of selflessness in ministry. In 2 Corinthians, Paul speaks of abasing himself for others'' exaltation, while in Acts, he mentions ministering to his own needs and those with him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 8, 47, 11, 9, 9, 'to do you service', 'Support and Service in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of support in ministry. In 2 Corinthians 11:8, Paul mentions taking wages from other churches, while in 11:9, he highlights how the brethren from Macedonia supplied his needs, showing a reliance on others for service.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 8, 50, 4, 14, 16, 'taking wages of them', 'Support and Communication in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of financial support for ministry. In 2 Corinthians, Paul mentions ''taking wages'' from other churches, while in Philippians, he acknowledges the Philippians'' unique support during his affliction.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 8, 50, 4, 18, 18, 'to do you service', 'Support and Sacrifice in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of support in ministry, where Paul acknowledges receiving help from other churches to serve the Corinthians. Both passages emphasize the importance of contributions and sacrifices made for the sake of the Gospel.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 9, 52, 2, 6, 6, 'being burdensome', 'Burden and Support in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of not being burdensome to others while in ministry. They highlight the idea of relying on support from others rather than seeking to impose on those being served.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 9, 53, 3, 8, 9, NULL, 'Self-Sufficiency in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the commitment to not being burdensome to others. They highlight the effort to provide for oneself while serving others, demonstrating a shared principle of self-reliance in ministry.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
