(47, 11, 9, 44, 18, 3, 3, 'chargeable to no man', 'Paul''s Work Ethic and Support', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s commitment to self-sufficiency and labor. In 2 Corinthians, he notes he was ''chargeable to no man,'' while in Acts, he worked as a tentmaker, reflecting his dedication to not being a burden.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 9, 44, 20, 33, 33, 'chargeable to no man', 'Financial Integrity in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the rejection of personal gain. Paul asserts he has not coveted others'' possessions, reflecting his commitment to not being a financial burden.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 9, 47, 6, 4, 4, NULL, 'Ministry and Support in Affliction', 'Both passages emphasize the challenges faced by ministers of God. In 2 Corinthians 11:9, Paul mentions his needs being supplied, while 2 Corinthians 6:4 highlights enduring necessities and distresses. This connection highlights the theme of reliance and support in ministry.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 10, 45, 9, 1, 1, 'the truth of Christ is in me', 'Truth in Christ Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the truth in Christ, highlighting the speaker''s commitment to honesty. The phrase ''I say the truth in Christ'' in Romans parallels the assertion of truth in 2 Corinthians.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
