(47, 11, 16, 47, 11, 21, 23, NULL, 'Boasting in Weakness', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s willingness to boast foolishly about his credentials and sufferings. The phrase ''I speak as a fool'' in the target passage directly connects to his earlier invitation to be received as a fool for boasting.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 11, 16, 47, 12, 11, 11, 'as a fool', 'Paul''s Boasting as a Fool', 'This connection highlights Paul''s self-identification as a fool in both passages. In 2 Corinthians 11:16, he invites others to receive him as a fool, while in 12:11, he acknowledges becoming a fool in glorying.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
