(47, 11, 30, 47, 11, 16, 18, 'glory of the things which concern mine infirmities', 'Boasting in Infirmities', 'Both passages emphasize the act of boasting, with Paul contrasting his glorying in weaknesses against others who boast in fleshly achievements. This connection highlights the theme of true strength found in acknowledging one''s infirmities.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
