(47, 12, 11, 48, 2, 6, 14, 'the very chiefest apostles', 'Apostolic Authority and Recognition', 'Both passages emphasize the recognition of apostolic authority, with Paul asserting his equality with the chief apostles in 2 Corinthians and challenging Peter''s actions in Galatians. This connection highlights the theme of apostolic legitimacy and the struggle for acceptance within the early church.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
