(47, 12, 12, 45, 15, 18, 19, NULL, 'Signs and Wonders Connection', 'Both passages emphasize ''mighty signs and wonders'' as evidence of apostolic authority and the power of the Spirit in preaching the gospel. This connection highlights the role of miraculous acts in validating the ministry of the apostles.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 12, 12, 47, 4, 2, 2, 'signs of an apostle', 'Signs of Truth and Integrity', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of truthfulness and integrity in ministry. The ''signs of an apostle'' in 2 Corinthians 12:12 demonstrate the authenticity of Paul''s ministry, while 2 Corinthians 4:2 highlights the rejection of deceit in handling God''s word.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 12, 12, 47, 11, 4, 4, NULL, 'Signs of Apostles and False Teachers', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of authentic signs and teachings. The mention of ''another Jesus'' in 2 Corinthians 11:4 suggests a contrast to the genuine signs of an apostle described in 12:12.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(47, 12, 12, 43, 4, 48, 48, NULL, 'Signs and Wonders Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of signs and wonders in relation to belief. In 2 Corinthians, the signs of an apostle are highlighted, while John points out that belief is contingent upon witnessing such signs.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
